      <p class="project_body">
        For my senior thesis I wanted to explore through research how people are using their phones and try to find answers to the question if people are distracted with their phones and why. One day I was waiting for my subway and noticed that 99% of people were on some sort of mobile device. This was extremely interesting to me because I started asking questions. <i>What are these people looking at? Why is it so easy to look at our phones? What prompts us to use our phones in time of waiting? Isn't there a better way to spend our time instead of looking at a phone endlessly?</i> Throught this research I aimed to discover and understand why it is so easy to use our phones and what we perceive as a waste of time in the modern context.
      </p>
