        <u>Insight 1:</u> People are most likely to use their phone in times of idleness and waiting. Essentially, things like waiting in line or being still is a greater waste of time than being on the phone.
      </p><br>

      <p class="project_body">
        <u>Insight 2:</u> The phone is incredibly easy to use. Most of the functions on the mobile device can be used with one hand.
      </p><br>

      <p class="project_body">
        <u>Insight 3:</u> The phone instills a sense of security. In situations where people are uncomfortable (in the elevator with strangers), they would pull out their phones and look at them even if all they did was unlock the phone, swipe the home screen a couple times accomplishing nothing.
      </p><br>
